groundTruth.text:
Abstract
                Objective
                The outbreak of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus 2 (SARS-COV-2) has caused more than 26 million cases of Corona virus disease (COVID-19) in the world so far. To control the spread of the disease, screening large numbers of suspected cases for appropriate quarantine and treatment are a priority. Pathogenic laboratory testing is typically the gold standard, but it bears the burden of significant false negativity, adding to the urgent need of alternative diagnostic methods to combat the disease. Based on COVID-19 radiographic changes in CT images, this study hypothesized that artificial intelligence methods might be able to extract specific graphical features of COVID-19 and provide a clinical diagnosis ahead of the pathogenic test, thus saving critical time for disease control.
              
                Methods
                We collected 1065 CT images of pathogen-confirmed COVID-19 cases along with those previously diagnosed with typical viral pneumonia. We modified the inception transfer-learning model to establish the algorithm, followed by internal and external validation.
              
                Results
                The internal validation achieved a total accuracy of 89.5% with a specificity of 0.88 and sensitivity of 0.87. The external testing dataset showed a total accuracy of 79.3% with a specificity of 0.83 and sensitivity of 0.67. In addition, in 54 COVID-19 images, the first two nucleic acid test results were negative, and 46 were predicted as COVID-19 positive by the algorithm, with an accuracy of 85.2%.
              
                Conclusion
                These results demonstrate the proof-of-principle for using artificial intelligence to extract radiological features for timely and accurate COVID-19 diagnosis.
              
                Key Points
                • The study evaluated the diagnostic performance of a deep learning algorithm using CT images to screen for COVID-19 during the influenza season.
                • As a screening method, our model achieved a relatively high sensitivity on internal and external CT image datasets.
                • The model was used to distinguish between COVID-19 and other typical viral pneumonia, both of which have quite similar radiologic characteristics.

templateData.title: AI-Driven Radiological Feature Extraction for Accelerated Disease Diagnosis
templateData.description: Technical template for developing and evaluating AI models that extract diagnostic features from radiological images (X-ray, CT, MRI) to accelerate infectious disease detection, with emphasis on computational efficiency, scalability, and integration with clinical workflows.

templateProperty.label: Data type
templateProperty.description: The type of radiological imaging used as input (e.g., X-ray, CT, MRI, Ultrasound).

templateProperty.label: Primary Dataset
templateProperty.description: Private dataset

templateProperty.label: Dataset Size
templateProperty.description: 1065 CT images

templateProperty.label: Image Resolution (Width x Height)
templateProperty.description: Standardized input resolution for the model (e.g., 224x224, 512x512).

templateProperty.label: Preprocessing Pipeline
templateProperty.description: Detailed steps for image normalization, augmentation, and artifact removal (e.g., histogram equalization, windowing for CT, noise reduction).

templateProperty.label: Feature Extraction Backbone
templateProperty.description: Base model architecture used for feature extraction (e.g., ResNet50, EfficientNet, Vision Transformer, 3D CNN).

templateProperty.label: Custom Layer Configuration
templateProperty.description: Description of custom layers added to the backbone (e.g., attention mechanisms, spatial pyramids, multi-scale fusion).

templateProperty.label: Model Parameters (Total)
templateProperty.description: Total number of trainable parameters in the model.

templateProperty.label: Training Framework
templateProperty.description: Software framework used for model development (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX).

templateProperty.label: Hardware Accelerator
templateProperty.description: Primary hardware used for training/inference (e.g., NVIDIA A100, TPU v4, CPU-only).

templateProperty.label: Batch Size
templateProperty.description: Number of samples processed in a single forward/backward pass.

templateProperty.label: Optimizer
templateProperty.description: Optimization algorithm used (e.g., Adam, SGD, RMSprop).

templateProperty.label: Learning Rate
templateProperty.description: Initial learning rate used during training.

templateProperty.label: Learning Rate Schedule
templateProperty.description: Strategy for adjusting learning rate (e.g., cosine decay, step decay, plateau reduction).

templateProperty.label: Training Epochs
templateProperty.description: Total number of epochs the model was trained for.

templateProperty.label: Early Stopping Patience
templateProperty.description: Number of epochs to wait before early stopping if validation metrics plateau.

templateProperty.label: Loss Function
templateProperty.description: Primary loss function used (e.g., cross-entropy, Dice loss, focal loss).

templateProperty.label: Class Imbalance Handling
templateProperty.description: Techniques used to address class imbalance (e.g., weighted loss, oversampling, SMOTE).

templateProperty.label: Inference Latency (ms)
templateProperty.description: Average time per image for model inference on target hardware (milliseconds).

templateProperty.label: Throughput (images/sec)
templateProperty.description: Images processed per second on target hardware (batch size = 1).

templateProperty.label: Primary Evaluation Metric
templateProperty.description: Main metric used to evaluate model performance (e.g., AUC-ROC, F1, sensitivity).

templateProperty.label: Primary Metric Score
templateProperty.description: Achieved score for the primary evaluation metric (e.g., AUC-ROC = 0.95).

templateProperty.label: Sensitivity (Recall)
templateProperty.description: True positive rate for disease detection.

templateProperty.label: Specificity
templateProperty.description: True negative rate for disease detection.

templateProperty.label: Precision
templateProperty.description: Positive predictive value for disease detection.

templateProperty.label: F1 Score
templateProperty.description: Harmonic mean of precision and recall.

templateProperty.label: False Negative Rate
templateProperty.description: Proportion of missed positive cases (critical for infectious diseases).

templateProperty.label: Confidence Calibration
templateProperty.description: Method used to calibrate model confidence scores (e.g., temperature scaling, Dirichlet calibration).

templateProperty.label: Explainability Method
templateProperty.description: Technique used to interpret model decisions (e.g., Grad-CAM, LIME, SHAP).

templateProperty.label: Deployment Framework
templateProperty.description: Framework used for model deployment (e.g., TensorRT, ONNX, TFLite).

templateProperty.label: Model Quantization
templateProperty.description: Technique used to reduce model size (e.g., FP32 to INT8, pruning).

templateProperty.label: Clinical Integration Method
templateProperty.description: Approach for integrating model outputs into clinical workflows (e.g., DICOM integration, PACS plugin, EHR API).

templateProperty.label: Regulatory Compliance
templateProperty.description: Standards adhered to for clinical use (e.g., FDA 510(k), CE Marking, HIPAA).

templateProperty.label: Benchmark Comparison
templateProperty.description: Named benchmarks or prior works the model was compared against (e.g., radiologist performance, state-of-the-art models).

templateProperty.label: Limitations and Failure Modes
templateProperty.description: Documented scenarios where the model underperforms (e.g., rare diseases, low-quality images, edge cases).

templateProperty.label: Data Collection Period
templateProperty.description: Timeframe during which the dataset was collected (e.g., 2020-2023).

templateProperty.label: Source Code Repository
templateProperty.description: Link to the public/private repository hosting the implementation.

templateProperty.label: Paper DOI
templateProperty.description: Digital Object Identifier for the published work (if applicable).
